# Privacy Policy for SnapMyShift

Effective date: [04/12/2026]

SnapMyShift helps users scan work schedules, create alarms, and manage shift information.

## Information We Access

SnapMyShift may request access to:

* Camera, to let users capture schedule images for scanning
* Photos or selected media, if the user chooses an image from their device
* Calendar, if the user chooses to export shifts to their calendar
* Notifications and alarms, to create shift reminders

## How We Use Information

We use this information to:

* scan and process schedule images
* extract shift details
* create alarms and reminders
* export shifts to the user’s calendar when requested
* provide premium subscription features

## Image Processing

If a user scans a schedule, the image may be securely transmitted to our service providers for processing so shift data can be extracted.

## Data Storage

Shift data, alarms, and settings may be stored on the device. Some data may also be processed or stored by backend services used to operate the app.

## Sharing

We do not sell personal data. We may share data only with service providers needed to operate app features, such as image processing or subscription services.

## Subscriptions

Premium subscriptions are managed through Google Play. Billing information is handled by Google.

## Security

We take reasonable steps to protect user data during transmission and storage.

## Data Deletion

Users may delete saved schedules and app data from within the app or by uninstalling the app. Users may also contact us with deletion requests.

